excerpt: Medieval palace exhibiting the artworks, weapons & antiquities collected by its 20th-century owner.
detail_description: Palazzo Falson, also known as the Norman House, is a well-preserved medieval palace in Mdina, dating back to the early 14th century. The house boasts beautiful double windows from the 15th century and has a colorful history, including ownership by Matteo Falsone and Captain Olof Gollcher. The latter amassed an eclectic collection of antiques, which now form a fascinating display at the museum.
name: Palazzo Falson
address: Villegaignon Street, Triq IL Villegaignon, Mdina, Malta

excerpt: Exhibits on the history of corporal punishment in  cells & passageways beneath a medieval palace.
detail_description: The Mdina Dungeons Museum, located in the historic town of Mdina in Malta, offers a captivating exploration of the city's dark past. Housed within 17th-century vaults beneath the city, this museum was once used as prison cells during the time of the Knights of Malta. Now converted into a museum, it showcases instruments of torture and restraints used to control prisoners. Visitors can wander through narrow corridors and cramped cells while learning about Malta's violent history.
name: The Mdina Dungeons Museum

excerpt: Built 1696–1705, the country's oldest church features Baroque frescoes, engravings & other artworks.
detail_description: St. Paul's Cathedral, located in Mdina, Malta, is a historic church dating back to 1696-1705. The cathedral features Baroque frescoes, engravings, and other artworks that survived a violent earthquake in 1693 which destroyed the earlier Norman church on the site. The interior boasts intricate 17th-century apse mural 'The Shipwreck of St. Paul' by Mattia Preti and 900-year-old Irish bogwood sacristy doors.
name: St. Paul's Cathedral
address: 2 Triq San Pawl, Mdina MDN 1061, Malta

excerpt: Historic building with a collection of sacred art & objects, including coins, documents & relics.
detail_description: The Mdina Cathedral Museum is a must-visit for history enthusiasts. Housed in a Baroque building dating back to the early 1700s, it was originally a seminary and now showcases an impressive collection of sacred art and objects. The museum features diverse displays including religious artifacts such as embossed choir books, paintings acquired over the ages, and works of art bequeathed by a private collector.
name: Mdina Cathedral Museum

detail_description: Fontanella Tea Garden is a popular cafe in Mdina known for its delicious homemade cakes and stunning views of Malta. It offers a variety of light meals, including sandwiches, pastizzi, and pizzas. The intimate wine bar with fairy lights creates a charming atmosphere at night. Visitors can also savor the traditional Maltese ftira while enjoying the panoramic scenery from the bastion walls.
name: Fontanella Tea Garden

excerpt: A stone bridge leads to this elegant 1700s gate to a citadel with medieval & baroque architecture.
detail_description: Mdina Gate is an elegant 1700s gate that leads to a citadel featuring medieval and baroque architecture. Located in Mdina, Malta, this historic site was once the stronghold of the island's medieval, Arab-influenced nobility. The city, which means 'city' in Arabic, boasts a 3000-year history and sits atop a hill with commanding views across the island.
name: Mdina Gate

excerpt: Mdina, also known by its Italian epithets Città Vecchia and Città Notabile, is a fortified city in the Western Region of Malta which served as the island's former capital, from antiquity to the medieval period. The city is still confined within its walls, and has a population of 250. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Mdina, also known as Città Vecchia and Città Notabile, is a historic fortified city in Malta's Northern Region. It was the island's former capital from ancient to medieval times and remains enclosed within its walls with a population of 250. Triq ta Vnezja, or Venice Street, is a charming narrow pedestrianized street within Mdina offering stunning panoramic views of the Maltese countryside.
name: Mdina

excerpt: 18th-century palace with natural history exhibits, including many focused on the local ecosystem.
detail_description: Nestled within the stunning Vilhena Palace, an 18th-century baroque gem in Mdina, the National Museum of Natural History is a treasure trove for anyone fascinated by the natural world. This captivating museum showcases nearly one million specimens that highlight Malta's rich biodiversity and historical significance.
name: National Museum Of Natural History

detail_description: Located in the northern part of Mdina, Malta, the Carmelite Priory is a 17th-century monastery that provides a rare glimpse into monastic life. The friars living here are open to sharing their daily routines with visitors. The Church of the Annunciation within the priory boasts high ceilings, remarkable art pieces, and an impressive dome. Guided tours offer access to various areas including the refectory, kitchens, and typical accommodation cells.
name: Carmelite Priory
address: VCP3+P5H, Carmelite Priory, Triq IL Villegaignon, Mdina, Malta

detail_description: When exploring the enchanting city of Mdina, a visit to the Knights of Malta exhibit is an absolute must for history enthusiasts. Nestled within the ancient walls and adjacent to Casa Magazzini—an ammunition store dating back to the 1500s—this immersive experience transports you through time.
name: The Knights Of Malta

detail_description: Mdina, also known as the Silent City, is home to several impressive sights such as Vilhena Palace, Palazzo Falson (Norman House), and St. Paul's Cathedral with its exquisite marble gravestones. One of the top attractions in Mdina is The Mdina Experience, where visitors can watch a 25-minute movie uncovering the city's mysteries and history. Additionally, tourists can explore the Chapel of St.
name: The Mdina Experience

excerpt: Visitors can tour a portion of this large, ancient Roman underground cemetery complex.
detail_description: St Paul's Catacombs, located near the church, are an extensive ancient Roman underground cemetery complex dating back to the 3rd century AD. Used for burials for around 500 years, this atmospheric labyrinth of rock-cut tombs, narrow stairs and passages offers a unique historical experience. The site includes a visitor center offering self-guided audio tours that provide insights into the catacombs' history and significance.
name: St Paul’s Catacombs

excerpt: Rabat is a town in the Western Region of Malta, with a population of 11,497 as of March 2014. It adjoins the ancient capital city of Mdina, and a north-western area formed part of the Roman city of Melite until its medieval retrenchment. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Rabat, a charming town in the Northern Region of Malta, is home to around 11,497 people. It is closely connected to the ancient capital city of Mdina and has historical significance dating back to Roman times. Visitors can explore its small and walkable streets with lovely architecture and intriguing back alleys. A must-see attraction is the catacombs of St. Paul's Cathedral, offering a bizarre and eerie experience that adds to the town's allure.
name: Rabat

detail_description: De Mondion Restaurant is one of the top restaurants in Mdina, Central Malta, offering Mediterranean and Middle Eastern cuisine. It has been recognized as a must-visit dining destination, alongside other renowned eateries in the area. The restaurant's culinary offerings have garnered praise and accolades, making it a popular choice among locals and visitors alike. With its exquisite dishes and inviting ambiance, De Mondion Restaurant provides a delightful dining experience that captures the essence of the region's vibrant food scene.
name: The de Mondion Restaurant

detail_description: Bastion Square is a charming spot located at the edge of Mdina's Citadel walls, offering a stunning view of the surrounding landscape. The square is surrounded by impressive golden sandstone buildings adorned with colorful shutters and grand doors. It provides an excellent vantage point to admire Malta's picturesque scenery of farmlands and rolling hills. Visitors can also explore nearby attractions such as St.
name: Bastion Square

detail_description: Mdina Glass, established in 1968, showcases the art of traditional glassblowing techniques where skilled artisans transform raw materials into vibrant molten glass. The store offers a diverse range of colorful glassware including vases, bowls, perfume bottles, candleholders, figurines and lamps. Visitors can explore a wide selection of glass products with varying prices based on size and intricacy. Customers have also reported receiving friendly service and even small discounts on their purchases.
name: Mdina Glass (Mdina)
address: St Publius Square Mdina, MDN 1010, Malta

detail_description: Pjazza Mesquita, a small historic square located just a few minutes from Mdina Gate in Malta, is renowned as one of the iconic filming locations for Game of Thrones. This picturesque square was used as the exterior of Littlefinger's brothel in the series. Visitors can explore this charming spot and enjoy some nice eateries while taking in the historical ambiance.
name: Pjazza Mesquita

detail_description: Palazzo Santa Sofia is a must-see attraction in Mdina, Malta. It is the oldest surviving building in the city, with its first floor dating back to 1233. The upper floor was added in the 20th century. This inconspicuous yet remarkable structure features a large black arched door and is located near the cathedral square on a narrow street. Once a residential house from the 13th century, it now stands as an important historical landmark.
name: Palazzo Santa Sofia
address: VCP3+H62, Triq Santa Sofija, Mdina, Malta

name: Church of the Annunciation of Our Lady
address: VCP3+M5Q, Kunvent tal-Karmnu, Triq Villegaignon,, L-Imdina, Malta

detail_description: Howard Gardens is a beautiful and freely accessible park located at the border between Mdina and Rabat in Malta. It offers a relaxing stroll through lush greenery, an orange tree orchard, statues, benches, and public toilets. Visitors can enjoy a tranquil afternoon amidst the well-maintained plant life or take a leisurely walk during summer evenings when the crowds thin out.
name: Howard Gardens

detail_description: The Torre dello Standardo, built in 1725 by the Order of St John, is a significant part of Malta's historical and architectural heritage. This stone watchtower served as a crucial link in the island's communication system, relaying signals to other coastal towers to raise alarms or pass on messages in case of attack. Adorned with intricate detailing, it stands near the Main Gate within Mdina's fortifications.
name: Torre dello Standardo

excerpt: Open-air remains of a 1st-century BCE Roman house & a museum showcasing mosaics from the site.
detail_description: Located in Rabat, Malta, Domvs Romana is an open-air site featuring the remains of a 1st-century BCE Roman townhouse. The discovery of this ancient house led to the establishment of the Domus Romana Museum, which now safeguards the excavated ruins and displays a remarkable collection of Roman artifacts found in Rabat and neighboring Mdina. Visitors can marvel at well-preserved mosaic floors that showcase the craftsmanship employed in constructing homes for affluent Romans.
name: Domvs Romana

detail_description: Greek's Gate is the second entrance to Mdina, featuring a less elaborate design compared to the main gate. Dating back to the medieval era, it received a baroque-style outer structure in 1724 by Charles Francois de Mondion. This addition resulted in the gate now comprising two vaulted gateways, adding an interesting historical and architectural dimension to this ancient city.
name: VCP2+7MF Greek's Gate

excerpt: Museum with paintings of key events taking place in Malta's old capital from medieval times to WWII.
detail_description: Tales of The Silent City, located in Mdina, Malta's old capital, is a museum showcasing paintings depicting key events from medieval times to WWII. Mdina, also known as Melite in Roman times, boasts a rich history dating back to the 8th century BC. The city's fortified walls and labyrinthine streets offer visitors a glimpse into its storied past.
name: Tales of The Silent City

detail_description: The Fork and Cork restaurant offers a Mediterranean and European menu, located about 3.6 km away from the Percy Jackson Book Order. It is known for bringing out the carnivore in the omnivore with its juicy steaks, creating a true connection with nature. The restaurant provides a dense, nutty cake filled with flavors from almonds, honey, and orange rinds - a rich indulgence often served during weddings and celebrations.
name: The Fork and Cork Restaurant

detail_description: Trattoria AD 1530 is a charming eatery located in the quiet old square of Mdina, next to the boutique Xara Palace Hotel. It offers traditional and delicious cuisine, making it perfect for any occasion. The restaurant features umbrella-shaded tables for al fresco dining and an equally charming interior with high arched ceilings and old carpentry tools adorning the walls.
name: Trattoria AD 1530
address: L, 2 Triq San Pawl, Mdina MDN 1061, Malta

name: Blue Mdina Door
address: St Agatha's Esplanade Mdina, MDN 1160, Malta

detail_description: The Tools, Trades and Traditions Museum in Mdina is a nice collection of old tools and implements. It has some devices that awaken memories.
name: Tools, Trades and Traditions Museum
address: Palazzo de Piro, 3, Triq is-Sur Mdina MDN, 1050, Malta

detail_description: Located on Villegianon Street, the Banca Giuratale is a historic building in Mdina, Malta. Built in 1730 as the new Universita, it features a stunning portal adorned with armor, arms, and flags. The roof sculptures symbolize the Knights' military power and their rule over Mdina. This baroque-style structure served as the city's administrative council and courts.
name: Banca Giuratale

detail_description: Bastions Brew cultured cafe is a charming cafe and bar situated in the heart of Rabat, offering a lovely location to relax and enjoy the surroundings. It provides various viewpoints along the defensive walls where visitors can admire stunning views of the Maltese countryside. One popular spot is located near the blue door, providing an excellent vantage point for gazing out across the landscape.
name: Bastions Brew cultured cafe

detail_description: The Malta Aviation Museum is a paradise for aircraft enthusiasts, situated on the former Royal Air Force station. It features a remarkable collection of aircraft, including a WWII Spitfire Mk IX and a Hawker Hurricane IIa that were salvaged from the sea after 54 years. The museum also showcases other vintage planes such as a Flying Flea, De Havilland Vampire T11, Fiat G91R, and Douglas Dakota DC-3.
name: Malta Aviation Museum

detail_description: Is-Serkin - Crystal Palace Bar is a must-visit spot in Mdina, Malta. After exploring the area, consider indulging in some of the best Maltese pastizzi at this charming bar located just opposite Mdina's entrance. You can also grab an ice-cream from one of the nearby vendors and take a leisurely stroll through the lush green gardens surrounding Mdina's fortress walls.
name: Is-Serkin - Crystal Palace Bar

excerpt: Grand 16th-century palazzo featuring an elegant interior & guided tours of the house & garden.
detail_description: Casa Bernard is a 16th-century palazzo located in Rabat, offering guided tours of its elegant interior and beautiful garden. The palazzo provides insight into the lives of Maltese nobility, with descendants of the original owners still residing on the premises. Visitors can explore a collection of important furniture, paintings, and objets d'art that were previously kept private. The house features fabulous antique furniture, silver items, and other intriguing antiques.
name: Casa Bernard

excerpt: Christian art & artifacts displayed in an 18th-century structure with catacombs & a famous grotto.
detail_description: Housed in an 18th-century building, The Wignacourt Museum is a former hostel for pilgrims visiting St. Paul's Grotto that now showcases a diverse collection of Christian art and artifacts. Visitors can explore the religious relics amassed by the local parish over the years, including wooden sculptures, vestments, and somber paintings by Francesco Zhara. The museum also offers access to St. Paul's Grotto, a revered site where St.
name: The Wignacourt Museum

detail_description: Mdina is a well-preserved medieval fortified town that offers a serene and peaceful atmosphere. The ancient architecture and narrow streets create a feeling of stepping back in time, especially on sunny days when the contrast between sunlight and shadows is striking. Despite being popular with tourists, the absence of motorized vehicles maintains its tranquility. Visitors can enjoy stunning views from eateries along the walls, such as Fontanella, and experience the enchanting ambiance of the Silent City at night.
name: Mdina

detail_description: The Greeks Gate, situated near the southwest corner of Mdina, is one of the two main entrance gates to the old medieval city. It was named after a small Greek community that once resided nearby. Dating back to 1724, this gate underwent a baroque transformation by architect Charles Francois de Mondion. Historically, it served as the exclusive entry point for slaves into Mdina.
name: Greeks Gate

detail_description: Mdina Old City Fortress in Malta is a captivating destination that offers a blend of medieval and baroque architecture, creating a rich historical experience. The ancient walled city boasts narrow, winding streets that make visitors feel like they've stepped back in time. The yellow buildings adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures showcase the area's architectural wonders. Wandering through the maze-like stone streets reveals delightful squares, charming restaurants, and beautiful churches.
name: Mdina Old City Fortess
Casa Gourgion - A Nobleman's Home
address: Pjazza San Pawl, Mdina MDN 1100, Malta

detail_description: CHALK cafe eatery wine is a vegetarian-friendly cafeteria that serves European-style breakfast, lunch, and dinner with healthy, homemade food and delicious desserts. The upper floor offers terrace seating for a delightful afternoon experience. The restaurant has a small balcony table for two and offers a wide selection of alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks along with coffee. It's known for its great selection of local dishes, including the Maltese platter at good value.
name: CHALK cafe eatery wine

detail_description: Coogi's Pizzeria & Bistrot @ Palazzo Costanzo offers two distinct dining experiences, with a restaurant and tea garden as well as a pizzeria. The restaurant is housed in a beautiful building with a cozy inner courtyard for dining. While some diners were not fully satisfied with the food, others enjoyed the pizza and local rabbit dish. The staff are described as polite and attentive, contributing to the overall romantic atmosphere of the place.
name: Coogi's Pizzeria & Bistrot @ Palazzo Costanzo
address: 29 Triq IL Villegaignon, Mdina MDN 1160, Malta

detail_description: Mdina is a must-see destination in Malta, offering a glimpse into the life and history of Medieval Malta. The city is incredibly beautiful with its narrow streets, ancient doors adorned with brass knockers, and the stunning St. Paul's Cathedral. Often referred to as the "city of silence," Mdina captivates visitors with its charm and historical significance. It's definitely worth a visit for anyone seeking to immerse themselves in the rich heritage of this enchanting city.
name: Mdina

detail_description: Hop on the Malta Fun Train Rabat, a charming trackless train resembling a 19th century locomotive that offers three different tour options: Rabat near Mdina, Valletta, or Bugibba. As you leisurely travel around, you'll be regaled with fascinating historical insights about the area and its landmarks. The hosts are known for their warm hospitality and the ride is both relaxing and informative.
name: Malta Fun Train Rabat

detail_description: The Blue Grotto Panoramic View Point is a must-visit destination in Malta, offering stunning views of the landscape. While it may not be easily accessible by car due to limited parking, taking bus 71 or 74 from Valletta is a convenient option. The bus ride takes about an hour and offers glimpses of the island's industrial areas. Once there, visitors can enjoy picture-perfect moments and even interact with a falconer and his bird for a small donation.
name: Blue Grotto Panoramic View Point

detail_description: The garden Il-Foss is a small and peaceful place located in the heart of Mdina, Malta. It has been landscaped and upgraded recently, making it a great place to walk and relax. You can access the garden from either the small parking area at Greeks Gate or from a staircase near il-Veduta restaurant. The gate, which was built in the medieval period, is named after a Greek community that once lived close to the site.
name: il-Foss

excerpt: Religious landmark rebuilt after WWII, with a prominent dome, marble floors & a virgin painting.
detail_description: Bażilika Santwarju tal-Madonna tal-Karmnu, also known as the Basilica of Lady of Mount Carmel, is a significant religious site in Valletta. This Roman Catholic church boasts a prominent dome and marble floors, with a striking neo-gothic design that overlooks the Sliema waterfront. It's part of the UNESCO World Heritage Site encompassing Valletta.
name: Bażilika Santwarju tal-Madonna tal-Karmnu
address: Triq it-Teatru l-Antik, Valletta VLT 1449, Malta

detail_description: Nestled on the picturesque island of Comino, Santa Marija Battery stands as a testament to Malta's rich history. Constructed between 1715 and 1716 by the Order of Saint John, this coastal artillery battery was designed to safeguard the South Comino Channel. Today, it remains one of only three surviving coastal batteries in Malta, featuring original 24-pounder cannons that evoke a sense of nostalgia for times gone by.
name: Santa Marija Battery
